timeline.bodyText:
I think you should add to docs how you intend users to use this method. I am imagining something like this:
@Autowired
FirestoreTemplate template;

template.withRoot(user1).delete(...)
template.withRoot(user2).find(...)

Also I think we should consider renaming it from operationsWithParent to something like: withCollectionRoot(...), withRoot(...), or withParent(..), etc. The method name should be short and also be clear that we are doing our operations from a different parent other than /.

